<user_id>118015902737883251161<//user_id><user_name>Matt Allen< /user_name><time>1614092224793< /time>< Rate>
1< /Rate>
< Text>
A very flakey company. I setup a measure in mid-December which went off without a hitch. Since then it has been crickets. I was told the install would be the second or third week in January. The first of February came so I called, was told that there was a delay and my install should be the next week. Now it is the end of February and no call, text, or email saying, "we are sorry for the delay". It has been nothing but silence. My job is quite small so I assume that it isn't important to this company. They must be harvesting only the big jobs which make the most money and the little guy is thrown on the back burner until further notice.
I have since found another company which came out, measured and installed in a 3 day period and did an amazing job!
Five Star Gutters needs to be renamed One Star Gutters unless you have a big money making job for them. Shame on them!< /Text>

< Review>
(This work was back in 2017. Adding this review from another site) Things were pretty good. Got an estimate within a day or two, and they were able to install within a 10 day window (they actually came out within 6 days). Prompt responses. Just two complaints: 1) They had to move a cable off of the eave and they didn't replace it. It's on the second story and I don't have a ladder to go up there and fix it, so it just flops around there in the wind and looks stupid. 2) When the wind blows a good bit down the side of the house, the gutters and downspout tend to groan. Not sure if this is because of the design, or poor installation.

Cindy saw my review on another review site and responded by sending out a crew to fix issue #1. They gave a 2 week window of when they could be back at my place to fix it, and instead they were there the next morning. Very great team!<//Review>

Put 5-Star Gutter on your call list, and don‚Äôt bother with anyone else.  They are the best!

1 Year Ago I wrote:  5 Star Rain Gutters of Atascadero CA came to our rescue when we were out of town for my mom's funeral.  We had a big rain and wind storm that took down the gutter by our kitchen while we were away.  A neighbor alerted us to the damage. They did the repair quickly and forwarded pictures of our house repair so we could drive home in ease! This is a company I will recommend to anyone looking to have new gutters installed or have help with any repair issues.  Very satisfied!  Truly deserves the name Five Star!<//text>

< Text>
Had them install some rain gutters on our new metal shop. After 6 weeks of waiting the made it out and did the install. $1000 later all looked good. Then we noticed there was a bunch of rattling in the wind. Gutters were solid but it was at that time we realized they had removed all of the roofline wall screws where the gutters were installed, and never re-installed them. This caused our new shop to leak water through the open screw holes and the top of the wall panels to vibrate as there was no longer anything supporting them. Called about getting some warranty work done, they said they couldn‚Äôt come out to just take a look for almost 4 weeks, during December and January during our Wet season.  They also took the screws they removed so we had to go buy new ones. Will update review as needed<//Text>

106271469113354447277<//user>
< Name>
Lawrence Thai< /Name>
<Time>1557789717577<//Time><rating>5</rating>< Review>
This is my favorite Pho place in the West Covina area. I have been coming here since I moved here in 2015 and my mom and I are grateful to have found it.

First the location. This place sits in a plaza across the street from the West Covina mall and sits in the same plaza as a PetsMart. There is always parking here as this plaza rarely gets packed.

The interior of this place is really traditional as there is hints of Vietnamese decor scattered throughout the walls. There is plenty of seating and the restaurant never gets to busy where you have to wait.

The Pho here is by far one of the top 10 I've had in my lifetime, and I've had my fair share. The broth for their food is nicely seasoned, not to salty, and not not salty enough. There is also plenty of noodles and meat despite whatever size you get. I always get the large Pho Dac Biet as I love variety in my Pho. I've had the opportunity to try their Boba Milk Tea a few times as they gave my mom and I a few samplers.< /Review>

Payam Larijani</name>
< time>
1489785846632< /time>
<resp>None<//resp>< Review>
A really nice and nostalgic coffee shop run by students.  A little bit crowded during the day obviously... but fast and friendly service.  The coffee seems a little watered down compared to coffee bean but it's still pretty good.  The pastries and snacks all seem over-priced and seem unhealthy and are probably full of High Fructose Corn Syrup and other cheap ingredients that make me fat.  I wish there was just a small cookie for 50 cents to have a bit or two with my coffee.  The place could really use a renovation but at the same time the classic setup reminds me of my days as a student.  I'm so glad UCLA didn't allow Starbucks or some other greedy corporation to do business on campus.  Please upgrade the piano, and add some real plants, change the carpet, maybe refurbish some of the other features.  Overall I give it 5 stars,  I love being able to sit by the windows and enjoy a little cool breeze from the courtyard.< /Review>

<text>This is a very nice looking Cafe on the 2nd floor of Kerckhoff Hall on the main UCLA campus.  The building is very impressive and historic.  The interior of the Cafe has alot of character with antique looking tables, chairs and medieval style windows.  There is also large courtyard seating next to the Cafe.

The Coffee, mixed blend, I had was very good as were the raspberry and cinnamon pastries.

This Cafe is very conducive to studying and meeting people in a warm, classical atmosphere.

The Staff is also excellent.< /text><Pics>None<//Pics><response>None</response>< gmapID>

<Review>The Willo is a Nevada County institution!  My parents went there for their 70th wedding anniversary dinner, I went there for a benchmark birthday.

Dinners include a salad with choice of dressing, baked beans, garlic bread and ice cream for dessert. Their drinks and house wine are reasonably priced and the wait staff and owners are friendly and fun.

I like the steaks, but have family members who like the halibut, and one whose book club sometimes meets there on Monday night for the ¬Ω Ground Choice NY Steak Hamburger Dinner (evidently taking advantage of unused meat from the weekend).

< Review>
What a great down home place. The New York steaks are awesome. They are cooked to exact perfection. Be sure and have reservations especially on the weekend as it fills up pretty fast. The staff was always coming by to make sure we had everything we needed. The plate comes looking beautiful with your juicy steak, the crispy basic salad and the yummy ranch beans. The potato is really good but a lot so my husband and I shared one. All around excellent meal.</Review>

<Review>From my experience, this is none like steakhouses in big cities.  This place did not give complementary all-you-can-eat bread and salad and the selection of starters (appetizers) was very small and overpriced.  So while I waited for my food (starving I might add), I had to sit and watch others eat.  Every other steakhouse I've been to had free bread and salad to munch on while you wait.  This place did not even have a choice of fries for a potato side.  The steak was so-so, but I ate everything and left still hungry.  At other steakhouses, I can't finish all my food and I pay WAY less than here.  I only came here because I was passing through had heard good reviews.  But I guess this place would be great to locals who have not been to up-scale restaurants in the big cities.< /Review>< Pictures>
None< /Pictures>

<Gmap_id>0x809b7ac20d3548df:0x31ff331cf6a7eddb</Gmap_id>< text>
If you love meat and a relaxed family-friendly setting, this is the stop for you!  We discovered the place by accident and were very pleasantly surprised!  This historic restaurant still uses the original quonset hut building as part of the bar area--very cool. With ribeye, my favorite cut, on Friday & Saturday only, I was a little skeptical of our weeknight visit, but the NY strip was yummy!  Stop on a Monday night for the fresh ground steak burgers created from the trimmings of the weekend. Super friendly atmosphere, exceptional service, and ice cream with dinner!  Reservations are suggested.</text>

This is a nice cozy, kitchy, one-off, fun place.  Which to me is always better than some corporate chain.  Most of us had the New York fillet which was great!  One had the ribs which looked so good I want to try them the next time we go there.  There was some discussion that they might cook the meat they serve on the done side, meaning a medium might be closer to a medium well.  I had a medium rare, which was absolutely perfect.  The salad which was made from ice-berg lettuce which was good, kind of felt like a blast from the past.  They offer a mixed-green salad which had other greens and beets as well as various veggies.  There were beans on the same plate as the salad and steak, which kind of feels like you're at a barbeque.  A baked potato came on its own plate along with a basket of delicious garlic bread  - both were again perfect.  Two thumbs way up!!</review>

< text>
We went for breakfast on a weekday. The place was empty. Its reputation as a pricy venue must have gotten around town. Being the only party in the dining room (there was one family outside finishing up) we had the server's attention.
They have specials now that fall more within the average person's budget, and the 2 of us ate for around $25 with food, coffee and tip. The food was well prepared, but unremarkable. We might go back and try the weekend menu, not certain though.<//text>

< user_name>
F U<//user_name>
<text>Very nice interior layout and design, great food and menu, bar area, pool table, wine cellar and dining area. Extremely friendly and competent staff who go out of their way to ensure your satisfaction. I had coffee, in large cup, and The Benny, eggs benedict, was almost perfect. Only thing wrong was poached eggs were over done and had no runny yolk. It also came with choice of hash browns, country potatoes, or fruit. I chose country potatoes which were fantastic. Have no major complaints or suggestions on how to improve this place as it has its own character which makes it what it is. For the location of this restaurant, it is a gem in a haystack that should be found. Located in the historical Springville Inn that has had paranormal activity.<//text></record></dataset><record>

< review>
Bought a LG nanocell90 TV here. Smooth experience. Was surprised to see not so full shelves and 2019 items still on display. Reason being their supply chain affected bad due to COVID19. They are now  prioritizing online orders, store and curb side pickups. If you don't find something, ask a sales person. They have everything in a storeroom somewhere and can get it to you in a couple of days. I guess this location has trucks running Tuesday and Thursday. Always do your research online before going there to avoid picking old items in shelves and reduce exposure to virus hanging in store trying to decide.<//review>

So chain store reviews will not differ a lot from one branch to the other.  Computers, TVs and cashier will always be located in the same spot.
We the human beings make the difference.
In this visit I asked for a computer power supply.  The person helping me never asked if it was for desktop computer or notebook so he ended up providing the wrong directions.  Nothing serious. Then I went to the store pickup line to grab something I ordered online.  The person assisting customers there was not good at all üëé.</Text>

<Text>My latest visit to this location was awful!
I went to buy a new computer - and had some specific questions.
So I roamed around that section looking at their offerings, and waiting for a chance to get some assistance from one of their sales associates.  But none of them paid any attention to me.  No eye contact, no scanning around to see who might be waiting to talk to them next.  Meanwhile they each spent very extensive periods of time with other customers.   Then they randomly engaged with other customers who came into that area well after me.  They seemed oblivious that I was even there, like maybe I was invisible.  At one point two associates spent a long time trying to persuade a customer to buy into some weird BB purchase club deal, while I stood right by watching them.  It was so weird!   And simply displayed a very poor awareness of how to juggle their time to best serve all customers, with some fair priority for who is next.
After 90 minutes I basically had to raise my assertiveness to get attention from one associate - who more-or-less answered my questions quite quickly, but was also very dismissive of a question I asked - as if I was asking something dumb, and he seemed quite impatient to spend any additional time with me, despite having just spent an hour with another customer.

< review>

<userid>116458210298398008235< /userid>< name>
Jeff Cheng< /name>
<Time>1560034192040</Time><Rate>3</Rate>< text>
Staff was knowledgeable, and prices can be good.

However, probably common to other people who work in similar stores, they tend to want you to buy more than you budgeted for.

I understand the concept of buying beyond your needs to be future proof, but in technology, there really is no such thing as future proof, and it may actually be cheaper to buy one system now and another when it's time to replace it than to buy one that is supposed to be future-proof.

Instead, I think it would have been better to recommend the most suitable system within the consumer's budget, than to recommend more powerful machines that cost hundreds/thousands more. (I.e. Choose a better processor, SSD, RAM, and/or graphics adapter, but not all, for similar prices)

If you can't utilize the extra power, it's just money (and extra electricity) wasted.

But overall, they have a good selection, and while the wait for available staff can be long, they are quite friendly.< /text>

<text>This review is for the extra coverage I purchased for a Sony Bravia TV couple years back. I bought this TV from Magnolia in Best Buy and they suggested that I purchase extra warranty because it was an expensive TV and I thought, better not worry about breaking and I purchased it. I can't exactly remember how much i paid for the warranty, but my guess is around 200-300 USD.

I still like the Sony TV but the issue was the remote that broke. TV came with two remotes. One regular remote and one that has a microphone in it that made searches very easy.

After the remote breaking, i went to the best buy store thinking they would help me replace it. Once they realized I wasn't there to buy something, i was quickly dismissed and was told to call their support and deal with them. I left the store annoyed but it wasn't a big deal. I called and spoke with a person on phone and they said they would ship it to the store only(Can't ship it to my house). Once it arrives, they were to give me a call.(promising right?).

Well that call never came and I gave up for a while.

Recently the second remote broke and I went in the store again and told the guy there about the story. He wasn't pleased to help but he tried anyway. He said that my remote was here but I never picked it up. I explained that I wasn't called and I surely wasn't going to best buy to check if my remote arrived.
He wasn't pleased with my answer and he kept looking down at the computer. I'd like to remind you that my external warranty hasn't expired yet I'm treated like I'm bothering these people over a remote.

After looking at the computer for a while, he told me that he doesn't know where the remote is and he's going to have to search the warehouse(?) He offered to give me a call if he finds it.

I was very frustrated at this point and I asked him how he thinks I should change channels and gave me the used remote they have in the store they use to change channels.

I was done at that point, I took the remote and left.

Never again.<//text><Pictures>None<//Pictures><Response>None</Response><gmap_id>0x808f7e2607fb2393:0x3982d3901a2dbc98</gmap_id></record>

<text>Pathetic customer service.
My Dad visiting from India needed to replace his phone which died suddenly. We indicated to the salesperson we were looking to get a Galaxy S9.
The salesperson was interested in closing the sale as soon as possible with minimum effort on his end, and could not even answer basic questions about what new features this model had. There was an obvious reluctance to even show a working model of the phone and upon doing so, a pressure to immediately bill and close the sale. Yet to see a salesperson that disinterested in his job :(
I've been to many Best Buy's across Atlanta and other parts of California and never had such a disappointing experience. I will not be returning to this location again. The quality of customer service is abysmal.< /text><Time>1558435436327< /Time>< Rating>

< text>
Although I detest browsing in this Best Buy on Harrison Street in San Francisco, due to the lack of service to older customers by indifferent teenage sales clerks, the store happens to be the most convenient Best Buy to where I live. Truth be told, I much prefer the ambience and service of the Best Buy at Geary & Masonic.

I'm elevating my rating of this place to 3-stars for one reason only. When you purchase an item online, and provided the Harrison Street outlet has it in stock, you can go within a few hours to the online pickup desk, adjacent to the checkout counter, and pick up your order, without having to deal with the surly sales clerks.</text>

I shopped from Best Buy before but the staff member whom I encountered in this particular one was rude. I went there to buy a MacBook, but I had no plan to take an Apple Care. I appreciate his good intention to help me secure my laptop, but insistence is not the best option to convince a customer. This store has some of the best customer service I have ever experienced. I came in because I was having issues with a laptop not turning on and I couldn't determine if the issue was with my laptop or the charger (it's the charger). The Geek Squad guy looked to see if they had appropriate extra parts for me, and an employee towards the back of the store allowed me to try plugging my computer into the charger that was at the chromebook station to determine that the laptop would indeed accept a charge (another employee helped me locate an appropriately similar model). Overall a great experience and I will be back.<//text>

<review>I ended up going to BB because Amazon failed me again on next day delivery of my law practice mission critical desktop computer power supply. This happens far too often when I select a particular product over others because it is promised the next day when I need it the next day. Anyway, I felt like a bit of a fool for not realizing that BB's prices, on power supplies at least, meet or beat Amazon's. Online options couldn't match Amazon for next day delivery, but I am realizing that Amazon's next day promise is not all that it's cracked up to be. So the selection of Gold rated PSUs was limited in the store, but it was guaranteed to be in my computer that day. And the price was better than the same model on Amazon. That doesn't really matter anyway because BB would have matched Amazon's price if it was lower. To top it all off, the sales guy took his time to check their inventory to give me as many options as possible. And he told me that I could return the PSU I bought from BB within 2 weeks even after it was installed as long as it wasn't damaged. So he suggested that I could return the PSU if I wanted to keep the one from Amazon when it finally arrived. Essentially, they don't mind if you buy theirs as a loaner. Even though I paid more for the one from BB, I am keeping it because I got more for my buck and I want to reward their terrific pricing and policies.</review>< Pictures>
None< /Pictures>

< Text>
I purchased a washer/dryer set from Best Buy store, after confirming they had the models in stock and would deliver within 2 days - I made it clear this was a dependency for the order (I had already researched two other purchase options, should Best Buy not be able to meet that need).

On the first deliver attempt, it was discovered that a 220v outlet was needed. (this had not been in the pre-delivery checklist, and the old set used 110v).  They would not do the delivery 'as is' (leaving the equipment and letting me plug it in when the wiring was complete). I chalked this up to "stuff happens", and had the wiring corrected the next day.

But the new delivery window was pushed for 5 days, and they had changed the model requested from electric to gas (which I only caught by accident).  On the next date they never showed up.  I called them and was informed they had come by, but my "street is too narrow for the delivery van and a smaller delivery truck would need to be scheduled".  My street is almost twice as wide as a standard car lane, and they had been here before so they should have known if there was going to be an issue.  I was blamed for not telling them about this 'special need'.  When I escalated the call, the supervisor refused to promise any date, and said I'd have to call again tomorrow because my delivery was still 'in transit'.

The next day they offered a date of one week out.  That date has not yet arrived, so there's still plenty of room for further problems and delays, and even if fulfilled, it will have been 3 weeks since my purchase and 3 full days of lost work for me.  While they have been civil, they have not been professional:  they attribute any issue as my fault and every reschedule goes to the bottom of their queue, rather than being treated as an escalation.<//Text>

< Review>
This Best Buy is sub par as far as electonics sales stores go. First off there are multiple armed guards at the entrance/exit that mad Dogg everyone that comes in no matter if you are 13 or 75...it's a little intimidating to say the least. The wifi in the store is so finicky that trying to test a laptop by surfing the web on it is impossible. The sales staff is mostly there to keep people from steeling stuff as they are very uneducated about the products. The last thing that makes this particular store sub par is 99% of everything in the store is tied down, locked, or is a piece of cardboard that you have to give to someone to go fetch it for you. I imagine because crime is so prevalent here. So ask yourself do you want to spend $500 in a store that has armed guards & every item under lock and key because people in the store are mostly theifs??? Not me, unless really desperate!<//Review>

NEVER EVER, EVER BUY A CAMERA HERE!!!!  Awful customer service!  We bought an $1800 camera before going on holiday and discovered it had issues.  All of the photos have black spots over them.  We took it back and they refuse to accept a return and say it needs to be sent to Sony or their Geek Squad (4 to 6 weeks turnaround)

We were unsure about the camera in the beginning and brought it back to the shop but the sales rep persuaded us to keep it, unpack it, and try it out properly.  We mentioned we were going on holiday for 10 days and he said it was not a problem if we came back in as soon as we came back.  We came in as soon as possible after arriving.

It might be convenient to buy items in Best Buy but use Amazon or somewhere with better customer service and a better return policy if there are issues with the electronics!

They are very friendly on the sales floor but are useless and unwilling to help on customer service!!</Text>

<user>115601224408975827494< /user><user_name>BROWNEYEZ 420< /user_name><Date>1484712160903< /Date><rating>3<//rating><review>It's hard to find a friendly sales associate willing to help you. They're standing around or don't work in the Section you need. They usually don't smile or walk up to say hello past the front door. I purchased a laptop last year out the box I had a really great guy salesperson. He was very knowledgeable, friendly, open to ask questions. In the end I got a great open box laptop that was top of the line at a great price. He gave me good advice and said if I had more questions I could call the store back or come in. I'm glad I came by that day it was raining hard outside but worth it every bit. The guy was named Steve big friendly guy. I can see why Best Buy hired him lol. I recently came to buy a pair of Beats headphones treating myself. My rep was not knowledgeable or friendly. But I was glad to get in and out and away from him. <userid>111109830728789022744<//userid><name>Richard Sizemore<//name>< Time>
1442429140443<//Time>
<rate>1<//rate><Text>Several months ago, I decided to purchase my first television. As I had never done such a thing, I thought I should go somewhere where they dealt with such a thing all day long. We pow-wowed over the things that I would need, and ultimately came down to a love 32" 1080p television, a roku3, and an insignia sound bar. Excited, and assured I had everything I needed to enjoy my new purchases, I poured myself into a cab and headed for home.

T.V. set-up was a breeze, but my first snag came when I opened the Roku. If you think that for $90, all of the necessary parts would be there, you'd be as surprised as I was. So, annoyed that I didn't actually have everything as I was told, I grabbed a book and called it a night.

The next day, venturing after work back to Best Buy, I has sold the HDMI cable that I wasn't the day before. "At last, victory shall be mine!" I quietly thought to myself as I headed for the closet bust stop that would take me home. Back home, I set up the roku, get my amazon and netflix accounts set up, and proceed to enjoy a movie. "huh, that's not a lot of sound coming from the sound bar" is my very first thought.

Naturally, there was no sound coming from it, though it was on and plugged in. Bummed with the thought that I had bought a bad bar, I used the bluetooth on my phone to see if it worked. Like a charm, I hear "this dude named Michael used to ride motorcycles" instantly thump out of the speakers. I surmise it must be the cord that is just no good, so I toss it and enjoy my movie with the T.V. speakers.

Round 3, I check again with an associate that I shouldn't be experiencing this issue, and I buy a new cord to plug into the bar and T.V. Still no sound. Really? Suffering a severe case of Forest Whittaker eye over this entire situation, I again just watch a movie and snooze.

Just last night, I finally decided to get the problem sorted once and for all. Or so I thought. 15 minutes waiting for an associate to be available to assist me, I describe my issue with the no sound, tell him which TV and sound bar I‚Äôve bought, and he sells me a ‚ÄòDigital Optical Audio Cable‚Äô, though I expressed concern that it didn‚Äôt look like anything on my sound bar would be a plug.

‚Äúits what you need.‚Äù

So home I went, no longer confident that anything I‚Äôm being told is true, but still crossing my fingers that it would work.

I‚Äôm sure you know by now that it did not.

In my attempt to avoid being incompatible hardware, buying things I did not need, not buying things I did need, and generally dealing with a giant debacle in my first TV purchase, I was handed that very thing at the hands what I was to believe were people smart on the issue. In a time that I could have bought everything on Amazon, for less, and had only myself to blame, I paid more to get raked over the coals.

I love Best Buy, the layout, the cleanliness, the assortment of selection. But for me, your customer service doth butter no parsnips. What I experienced is an example of a complete lack of proper training, knowledge, and on-going staff education that reflects extremely poorly of the management at this store. Save yourself and just buy it on Amazon.<//Text><pictures>None< /pictures><response>None</response><gmap_id>0x808f7e2607fb2393:0x3982d3901a2dbc98<//gmap_id></record>
